column2: Broward County School Districts are pure Swamp.
These teachers are out of hand

Bizarre.  This lacks the basic common sense you expect from someone in authority over children and to whom others look up to to set an example.  Based on his age, I would expect him to resign tomorrow, and definately before any legal conviction is rendered.  AKA:  Protecting the pension.  That is unless of course he can find an attorney to show everyone that:  'If the badge don't fit, you have to acquit!'  OK, OK, but who can forget O.J. Sinpson?!?  JUST SAYING...
